cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the evolution of wireless communication networks and proposes a heterogeneous networking architecture for 5G, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper mentions key technologies such as full duplex and cognitive-based approaches, which are related to information theory.
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper discusses various aspects of wireless communication networks, including spectrum access, device-to-device communication, and network densification, which are all related to communications and networking.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a cooperative framework for dynamic spectrum management, which involves system-level considerations and control.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the demand for high data rates and improved quality of service, which are related to multimedia applications.
